# Find the smallest x + y + z with integers x > y > z > 0
# such that x + y, x − y, x + z, x − z, y + z, y − z
# are all perfect squares.
# ----------------------------------------------------
# Analysis: brute force
#           Let x + y = A^{2}, x - y = B^{2}
#               y + z = C^{2}, y - z = D^{2}
#               x + z = E^{2}, x - z = F^{2}
#           Then, E^{2} = B^{2} + C^{2}
#                 F^{2} = B^{2} + D^{2}
#                 A^{2} = E^{2} + D^{2}
#                 C and D to be of the same parity


